subSection.paragraph:
The subfamily Rhyssalinae is phylogenetically one of the most basal taxonomic group within the family Braconidae and is currently represented by five extant tribes, Achaiabraconini Belokobylskij, 2009 , Acrisidini Hellén, 1957 , Histeromerini Fahringer, 1930 , Laibaleini Quicke, Butcher & Belokobylskij, 2020 , and Rhyssalini Foerster, 1963 (
Quicke et al . 2020
;
Jasso-Martinez et al. 2022
) and one recently described fossil tribe
Electroncophanini Belokobylskij & Zaldívar-Riverón, 2023
(
Belokobylskij et al . 2023
).

The material used for this study is deposited in the collection of the 
Kaliningrad
Amber Museum (KAM; 
Russia
).

subSubSection.paragraph:
Antenna (
Fig. 1C
) rather slender, filiform, weakly longer than body. Scape short and relatively narrow, without any transformations, ~1.3 × longer than its maximum width. Pedicel elongate and rather wide, about 0.7 × as long as scape. First flagellomere rather short and straight, longer than second flagellomere. Penultimate flagellomere rather wide and short, about as long as apical flagellomere; the latter acuminate apically.

Mesosoma (
Figs 1E, F
; 
2A
) not depressed. Pronotal neck short. Pronotum with wide and distinct posterodorsal lobe; its side with distinct, weakly curved and crenulate submedial furrow.Mesoscutum highly and subperpendicularly elevated above pronotum, distinctly and densely granulate. Notauli distinct and complete. Prescutellar furrow (scutellar sulcus) long, with high medial carina. Scutellum weakly convex, finely granulate. Mesopleuron mainly smooth. Precoxal sulcus distinct, wide, relatively short, rugulose. Propodeum convex, perhaps without lateral tubercles. with areas distinctly delineated by strong carinae.

Wings (
Figs 1A
; 
2E
). Fore wing hyaline; pterostigma rather long and relatively narrow. Radial (marginal) cell wide, not shortened, 2.5 × longer than its maximum width. Metacarp (1-R1) distinctly longer than pterostigma. Radial vein (r) arising weakly behind middle of pterostigma. First medial abscissa (1-SR+M) present and curved. Second radiomedial (submarginal) cell relatively short and tetragonal. Petiole (1-SR) of discoidal (discal) cell distinct, relatively long. Recurrent vein (m-cu) distinctly convergent with basal vein (1-M) towards posterior margin of wing. First mediocubital vein (M+CU1) well sclerotised and straight. Brachial (subdiscal) cell rather narrow and short; brachial vein (CU1b) perhaps present. Parallel vein (CU1a) not interstitial. Hind wing. Radial vein (SR) weakly sclerotised, entirely spectral. Nervellus (cu-a) present and closed relatively short submedial (subbasal) cell. Recurrent vein (m-cu) pigmented.

